Package com.rb.nonbiz.collections

Class NonContiguousRangeCollection<K extends java.lang.Comparable<? super K>>

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.collections.NonContiguousRangeCollection<K>
public class NonContiguousRangeCollection<K extends java.lang.Comparable<? super K>>
extends java.lang.Object
A collection of Ranges that may not be contiguous, and whose last range may or may not have an upper bound.

Strictly speaking this is 'not necessarily contiguous'. It could still be contiguous.

We're using <? super K> instead of <K> because there I may eventually want to have K be LocalDate, but LocalDate implements ChronoLocalDate which in turn implements Comparable<ChronoLocalDate>, so there's no other way to get this to work.

Note that we model all ranges (except maybe the last one) as closed, which is intentional for 'non-contiguous' (discrete) values. For e.g. doubles, this wouldn't work; we'd be representing this as e.g. [2, 5.5] and [5.5, 7] instead of [2, 5.5) and [5.5, 7], so there would be overlap. For e.g. integers, this does work; we'd be using e.g. [2, 4] and [5, 7], so there would be no gaps, but no range would be open on the right side.
